content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 9 ยง 4814.16 - Recapitulation of fees

State Regulations

At the end of the license period, a recapitulation shall
be made as between the licensee and the licensing authority with respect to the
gross rental received during the license period and the license fee previously
paid. Any deficiency of fee thereby established to be due shall be paid by the
licensee and, should said licensee apply for a license for a subsequent year, and in that event only, shall any excess of fee be credited to said
applicant. Notes
